php artisan scout:import "App\Models\Thread"

How It Works (Similar to StackOverflow):
Basic Search: Enter keywords (e.g., "elasticsearch help") – searches across title and content.
Advanced Filters: Use Elasticsearch query syntax like title:elasticsearch content:setup or title:(foo OR bar) for targeted searches, mimicking StackOverflow's operators.
Pagination: Works like recent threads.
Indexing: New/updated threads auto-index via Scout observers. Re-index manually if needed.
Expansion: For more SO-like features (e.g., tags), add a tags field to Thread and index it.
Test by creating threads, indexing, and searching. If issues, check Elasticsearch logs via docker logs forum_elasticsearch.